wikipedia_page.main: Henry Frederick Brophy (22 October 1916 – 6 November 1996) was an English professional footballer who played for Southampton in the years immediately before World War II. After the war, he emigrated to Australia where he coached and captained the national football team, including acting as team manager for two games in 1954 and 1955.

response: * Harry Brophy (born c. 1916), English football player and coach
* Harry Brophy, Arsenal (1936–1938) defender and coach of Australia (1954–1955).
